    {
      "id": "25ae8053fb0bc3c58a3df9a1c04a9151ee603edf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-23 17:22:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nsince James is working on a fix, let's drop it from the ready list meanwhile",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "d1ea6e8e6c8c6b1556ed02bc0edbdf835cd180fa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-23 19:52:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nJian brought out the following issues with the MDS definitions in this patch:\n1.\tIf SINGLEMDS is defined as something other than mds1 and if the Lustre version of SINGLEMDS is different from mds1, MDS1_VERSION cannot replace $(lustre_version_code $SINGLEMDS). Andreas said the MDS server versions are allowed to have a version difference of approximately +/- 0.0.4 . In our autotesting, we never test with different MDS versions, but I can’t comment on how other sites test w.r.t server versions. Is this a difference in MDS versions that we can tolerate in our test scripts? \n\n2.\tIf SINGLEMDS is defined as something other than mds1 and if the SINGLEMDS file system type is different from mds1, mds1_FSTYPE cannot replace $(facet_fstype $SINGLEMDS). I don’t see a way around having an mds1_FSTYPE and a singlemds_FSTYPE right now. \n\nIt is my understanding that SINGLEMDS is supposed to be used for commands that must be run on MDT0. We use “mds1” for this same purpose. Is there any reason to keep using SINGLEMDS? LU-6438 proposed removing SINGLEMDS. LU-7753 proposes renaming SINGLEMDS to ROOTMDS. The rename doesn’t seem necessary when we have and can use mds1. Any thoughts?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "81ef09f24653619e08f4ec7d3df86b599958c6aa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-23 21:15:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nMy preference would be to just remove SINGLEMDS.  While there is some chance in the future that we would allow removing MDT0000 from mds1 (e.g. if we mirror the root directory) it seems a far way off.  Also, we already have the mechanism to move the mds1 facet to another node, so I don't see a big benefit to keeping this separate.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "34e6c7d36ab509c1549c4709b04ec4b4e213c161",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-24 13:58:58.000000000",
